Description: This registry defines a representation of Boot Sources instances
Name: Dell Boot Sources Registry

Entry.DisplayName: Integrated NIC 1 Port 1 Partition 1: QLogic MBA Slot 1800 v7.14.2
Entry.Name: NIC.Integrated.1-1-1

Attributes.HelpText: This field tells the system where to find the operating system files needed for system startup. This field applies only when Boot Mode is 'BIOS'; it has no effect when Boot Mode is 'UEFI'.

Entry.DisplayName: AHCI Controller in Slot 7: A0S0 DELLBOSS VD
Entry.Name: AHCI.Slot.7-1

Attributes.HelpText: This field specifies the order in which hard-disk drives will be configured in the system. The first hard drive in the system will be the bootable C: drive in DOS/DOS-like operating systems. This field applies only when Boot Mode is 'BIOS'; it has no effect when Boot Mode is 'UEFI'.
